1
00:00:29,620 --> 00:00:32,980
=The Secret of the Lost Pearl=

2
00:00:33,020 --> 00:00:34,940
=Episode 20=
(Fiction. Do not imitate.)

3
00:01:05,510 --> 00:01:06,560
How's Lu?

4
00:01:07,400 --> 00:01:08,240
Lu,

5
00:01:08,950 --> 00:01:09,790
are you okay?

6
00:01:10,920 --> 00:01:12,510
What is this place?

7
00:01:13,200 --> 00:01:15,920
Have we already left the tomb?

8
00:01:16,430 --> 00:01:17,710
Are we out of danger?

9
00:01:19,280 --> 00:01:20,350
You're overthinking, Lu.

10
00:01:21,070 --> 00:01:21,910
Look.

11
00:01:22,280 --> 00:01:23,920
That big eyeball is still staring at us.

12
00:01:25,640 --> 00:01:26,640
What is that?

13
00:01:27,790 --> 00:01:28,870
Fireflies?

14
00:01:29,310 --> 00:01:30,840
Yeah, I think so.

15
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:32,326
I was looking at them for a while.

16
00:01:32,790 --> 00:01:34,120
How come these fireflies

17
00:01:34,280 --> 00:01:37,200
form an eyeball shape?

18
00:01:39,040 --> 00:01:40,510
If this were just a cave,

19
00:01:40,590 --> 00:01:42,120
we should have exited the tomb

20
00:01:42,120 --> 00:01:43,133
and entered the mountain.

21
00:01:44,230 --> 00:01:45,350
But it seems

22
00:01:45,480 --> 00:01:48,040
this eyeball pattern hides a secret.

23
00:01:50,710 --> 00:01:51,680
Anyway,

24
00:01:51,840 --> 00:01:53,350
we've walked here for so long.

25
00:01:53,710 --> 00:01:55,200
We've finally pieced together

26
00:01:55,760 --> 00:01:56,769
this tomb's information

27
00:01:56,780 --> 00:01:58,070
like a puzzle.

28
00:01:59,120 --> 00:02:00,590
Since this eyeball pattern

29
00:02:00,590 --> 00:02:02,950
is related to the curse on Chen Youxi,

30
00:02:03,400 --> 00:02:04,640
let's keep moving.

31
00:02:05,160 --> 00:02:06,040
Maybe

32
00:02:06,040 --> 00:02:07,120
when we piece together

33
00:02:07,120 --> 00:02:08,520
the truth,

34
00:02:08,910 --> 00:02:10,470
the curse can be lifted.

35
00:02:12,030 --> 00:02:12,880
Brilliant.

36
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:14,910
Brilliant, Ms. He.

37
00:02:14,910 --> 00:02:15,790
Chen,

38
00:02:15,800 --> 00:02:17,360
she's worried sick for you.

39
00:02:17,710 --> 00:02:18,560
Say something.

40
00:02:20,310 --> 00:02:21,710
Say something.

41
00:02:24,870 --> 00:02:26,030
Say a few words.

42
00:02:26,520 --> 00:02:28,120
- Ms. He...
- I'm going to scout out.

43
00:02:29,800 --> 00:02:31,840
Chen Youxi, what's wrong with you?

44
00:02:32,520 --> 00:02:34,240
Why so silent?

45
00:02:34,680 --> 00:02:36,430
She even played
The Phoenix Seeks a Mate.

46
00:02:36,520 --> 00:02:37,750
Tell her what you think.

47
00:02:37,750 --> 00:02:38,590
Enough.

48
00:02:39,430 --> 00:02:40,960
What attitude is that?

49
00:02:42,120 --> 00:02:42,960
Stop.

50
00:02:45,870 --> 00:02:47,030
Judge for yourself.

51
00:02:47,120 --> 00:02:48,750
How could Chen do that?

52
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:14,360
Right, when Lu woke up,

53
00:03:14,960 --> 00:03:16,280
I saw Bai Lingling

54
00:03:16,280 --> 00:03:17,430
take something out of her bag

55
00:03:17,710 --> 00:03:18,800
secretively.

56
00:03:19,800 --> 00:03:20,840
I'll be extra careful.

57
00:03:31,190 --> 00:03:32,030
Look.

58
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:38,430
The fireflies twinkling here.

59
00:03:41,520 --> 00:03:42,630
Pretty romantic, right?

60
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:44,960
Did you know

61
00:03:45,280 --> 00:03:47,000
that across the ocean in Ireland,

62
00:03:47,590 --> 00:03:48,430
there's a place

63
00:03:48,910 --> 00:03:51,470
called the Waitomo Cave?

64
00:03:51,750 --> 00:03:52,710
That's New Zealand.

65
00:03:57,400 --> 00:03:59,280
You've been there?

66
00:04:01,030 --> 00:04:01,910
Well.

67
00:04:02,310 --> 00:04:03,750
Tell me.

68
00:04:04,240 --> 00:04:05,560
Is it fun there?

69
00:04:05,560 --> 00:04:06,630
Are there fireflies?

70
00:04:06,641 --> 00:04:08,021
Would you understand if I told you?

71
00:04:09,153 --> 00:04:10,310
As long as you speak Chinese,

72
00:04:10,310 --> 00:04:11,430
I can understand every word.

73
00:04:11,840 --> 00:04:12,910
Wait a moment.

74
00:04:16,240 --> 00:04:18,270
Even if I don't understand,
you can teach me.

75
00:04:18,680 --> 00:04:20,070
You need to be kind.

76
00:04:21,270 --> 00:04:22,310
Shameless.

77
00:04:27,270 --> 00:04:29,750
The Phoenix Seeks a Mate
you mentioned...

78
00:04:31,630 --> 00:04:33,070
There's a lotus lamp here.

79
00:04:33,800 --> 00:04:35,600
The color is quite unique.

80
00:04:36,040 --> 00:04:36,880
Lotus lamp?

81
00:04:41,560 --> 00:04:42,400
Let's go see.

82
00:04:44,270 --> 00:04:45,310
Fire!

83
00:04:45,510 --> 00:04:46,350
Lu?

84
00:04:46,630 --> 00:04:48,270
Fire!

85
00:04:48,950 --> 00:04:50,510
Fire!

86
00:04:51,270 --> 00:04:52,110
Oh, no.

87
00:04:52,430 --> 00:04:53,310
My legs are burning.

88
00:04:53,310 --> 00:04:54,150
What happened?

89
00:04:54,160 --> 00:04:55,000
Come help me!

90
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:55,860
Lu!

91
00:04:55,870 --> 00:04:57,630
Come put out the fire!

92
00:04:57,630 --> 00:04:59,440
Put out the fire!

93
00:04:59,460 --> 00:05:00,340
Lu.

94
00:05:00,360 --> 00:05:01,640
- Lu.
- Hurry!

95
00:05:07,560 --> 00:05:08,400
Let me see.

96
00:05:09,160 --> 00:05:10,190
Does it hurt?

97
00:05:10,310 --> 00:05:11,600
Don't touch me.

98
00:05:12,510 --> 00:05:13,920
It's all burnt off.

99
00:05:14,190 --> 00:05:15,390
Good for you,

100
00:05:15,510 --> 00:05:17,190
burning yourself while warming up.

101
00:05:18,120 --> 00:05:19,750
What do you mean?

102
00:05:19,750 --> 00:05:20,830
Am I that stupid?

103
00:05:20,830 --> 00:05:22,240
Then what happened?

104
00:05:22,240 --> 00:05:23,430
I don't know.

105
00:05:23,430 --> 00:05:25,630
It just started burning.

106
00:05:25,720 --> 00:05:26,720
Where were you just now?

107
00:05:27,390 --> 00:05:28,510
Just a moment ago,

108
00:05:28,870 --> 00:05:30,560
I went to find a place to pee.

109
00:05:30,830 --> 00:05:31,830
I wandered around

110
00:05:32,120 --> 00:05:33,120
and went there.

111
00:05:33,583 --> 00:05:34,983
Then, I smelled something fragrant.

112
00:05:35,070 --> 00:05:36,950
I wondered who was roasting.

113
00:05:37,510 --> 00:05:38,800
And I caught fire.

114
00:05:39,360 --> 00:05:40,270
That's crazy.

115
00:05:41,920 --> 00:05:42,833
It's white phosphorus.

116
00:05:43,680 --> 00:05:44,520
White phosphorus?

117
00:05:45,040 --> 00:05:46,120
Where did it come from?

118
00:05:55,950 --> 00:05:58,160
The glowing on the cave ceiling
isn't fireflies;

119
00:05:58,630 --> 00:05:59,630
it's fluorite.

120
00:06:00,600 --> 00:06:03,040
The white phosphorus
was applied to the fluorite.

121
00:06:04,120 --> 00:06:05,310
When we made fire,

122
00:06:05,720 --> 00:06:07,000
the cave temperature rose,

123
00:06:07,680 --> 00:06:10,270
and the phosphorus fell on you.

124
00:06:13,830 --> 00:06:15,120
Luckily, you noticed it.

125
00:06:15,680 --> 00:06:16,950
If the fire kept burning,

126
00:06:16,973 --> 00:06:17,920
the temperature rising,

127
00:06:17,920 --> 00:06:19,040
everything would fall,

128
00:06:19,160 --> 00:06:20,566
and it could've set us all on fire.

129
00:06:21,680 --> 00:06:23,430
Chen, we can't stay here.

130
00:06:23,480 --> 00:06:24,600
Let's go.

131
00:06:24,600 --> 00:06:25,870
Go where?

132
00:06:25,870 --> 00:06:26,740
I just saw

133
00:06:26,740 --> 00:06:28,510
a light deep in the cave.

134
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:30,000
Light? What light?

135
00:06:42,250 --> 00:06:43,120
Is it there?

136
00:06:43,120 --> 00:06:43,960
Yes.

137
00:06:52,510 --> 00:06:53,350
What?

138
00:06:53,830 --> 00:06:55,950
Tell me.

139
00:06:56,360 --> 00:06:57,600
Am I the only one

140
00:06:57,600 --> 00:06:58,720
who finds this place creepy?

141
00:06:59,070 --> 00:07:00,270
You find

142
00:07:00,270 --> 00:07:01,480
everything creepy.

143
00:07:01,750 --> 00:07:03,830
No, I have a sixth sense.

144
00:07:04,330 --> 00:07:05,190
Trust me.

145
00:07:05,190 --> 00:07:06,030
Slow down.

146
00:07:06,720 --> 00:07:08,310
Take it easy.

147
00:07:08,310 --> 00:07:09,390
I'm fine.

148
00:07:10,120 --> 00:07:11,720
My sixth sense tells me

149
00:07:12,430 --> 00:07:14,070
this place is different

150
00:07:14,070 --> 00:07:14,910
from the others.

151
00:07:15,430 --> 00:07:16,600
How?

152
00:07:18,510 --> 00:07:20,560
The previous tunnels

153
00:07:20,560 --> 00:07:21,480
and chambers

154
00:07:22,040 --> 00:07:23,160
were cold.

155
00:07:23,750 --> 00:07:25,160
But this place...

156
00:07:25,480 --> 00:07:26,510
Is it warm?

157
00:07:27,800 --> 00:07:29,070
You must've peed.

158
00:07:29,360 --> 00:07:30,920
I'm telling you serious things.

159
00:07:31,510 --> 00:07:32,350
Smell it.

160
00:07:33,720 --> 00:07:34,560
What smell?

161
00:07:35,310 --> 00:07:37,720
A wild animal stench,

162
00:07:38,120 --> 00:07:39,270
like the lion and tiger area

163
00:07:39,270 --> 00:07:41,160
in the zoo.

164
00:07:41,160 --> 00:07:43,240
- Stop your nonsense.
- Really.

165
00:07:43,240 --> 00:07:44,682
You're so good at making up stories.

166
00:07:44,693 --> 00:07:45,560
When you get back,

167
00:07:45,560 --> 00:07:46,870
don't mess with your antiques.

168
00:07:46,870 --> 00:07:48,720
Set up a storytelling stall
on the bridge.

169
00:07:49,720 --> 00:07:50,680
I'll give you 0.5 yuan

170
00:07:50,680 --> 00:07:52,240
every day to boost your business.

171
00:07:52,270 --> 00:07:53,110
What do you think?

172
00:07:54,720 --> 00:07:55,950
What is this thing?

173
00:07:58,360 --> 00:07:59,240
What is this?

174
00:08:02,870 --> 00:08:04,510
Is that necessary?

175
00:08:04,800 --> 00:08:06,160
It's just a big bat.

176
00:08:07,270 --> 00:08:08,110
Bat?

177
00:08:10,190 --> 00:08:11,040
What a creepy place.

178
00:08:16,430 --> 00:08:18,480
Princess Xian'an,

179
00:08:19,070 --> 00:08:19,920
Xiangmu,

180
00:08:21,680 --> 00:08:24,240
Princess of Yan State,

181
00:08:24,240 --> 00:08:28,310
daughter of Li Kuo,
Emperor Dezong of Tang.

182
00:08:28,750 --> 00:08:29,800
I know this.

183
00:08:30,360 --> 00:08:31,200
Back then,

184
00:08:31,360 --> 00:08:32,670
The Huihu helped the Tang

185
00:08:32,670 --> 00:08:34,120
quell the An-Shi Rebellion.

186
00:08:34,670 --> 00:08:36,510
The Tang owed them a favor.

187
00:08:37,240 --> 00:08:39,150
The Huihu sent emissaries

188
00:08:39,390 --> 00:08:41,200
to request a marriage alliance.

189
00:08:41,790 --> 00:08:43,440
Li Kuo initially refused.

190
00:08:43,600 --> 00:08:45,150
He couldn't give up on his daughter.

191
00:08:45,150 --> 00:08:47,030
Later, Prime Minister Li Mi

192
00:08:47,030 --> 00:08:48,510
brought officials

193
00:08:48,550 --> 00:08:50,240
to pressure the emperor,

194
00:08:50,670 --> 00:08:52,480
forcing him to agree

195
00:08:52,480 --> 00:08:53,870
to this marriage alliance.

196
00:08:53,870 --> 00:08:55,600
Soldiers escorted Princess Xian'an

197
00:08:55,600 --> 00:08:56,870
to the Huihu.

198
00:08:57,080 --> 00:08:58,790
So, this tomb's owner

199
00:08:58,790 --> 00:09:00,720
is Li Kuo's eldest daughter,

200
00:09:00,720 --> 00:09:01,670
Princess Xian'an.

201
00:09:02,720 --> 00:09:04,480
That doesn't seem right.

202
00:09:05,030 --> 00:09:07,150
Historical records say

203
00:09:07,440 --> 00:09:10,840
Princess Xian'an died in the Huihu

204
00:09:11,080 --> 00:09:12,910
and never returned home.

205
00:09:13,360 --> 00:09:14,600
Many historical truths

206
00:09:15,320 --> 00:09:16,510
can't be recorded.

207
00:09:17,630 --> 00:09:18,470
Right?

208
00:09:18,630 --> 00:09:21,320
You can say that,

209
00:09:21,840 --> 00:09:23,630
but that doesn't make sense.

210
00:09:24,320 --> 00:09:25,750
Princess Xian'an married

211
00:09:25,750 --> 00:09:26,910
into the Huihu.

212
00:09:26,910 --> 00:09:28,790
She belonged to them.

213
00:09:29,200 --> 00:09:31,150
She was the Khatun,

214
00:09:31,630 --> 00:09:32,670
the Khan's wife.

215
00:09:33,120 --> 00:09:35,120
That was a prestigious position.

216
00:09:35,750 --> 00:09:36,840
After death,

217
00:09:37,360 --> 00:09:39,550
she'd have been buried properly

218
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:41,870
and carefully protected.

219
00:09:42,480 --> 00:09:43,390
How could she

220
00:09:43,720 --> 00:09:45,510
be sent back to the Tang secretively?

221
00:09:47,270 --> 00:09:48,150
Sorry.

222
00:09:48,270 --> 00:09:49,150
Besides,

223
00:09:49,750 --> 00:09:52,320
doing that is risky.

224
00:09:53,550 --> 00:09:55,200
Who could be so determined

225
00:09:55,320 --> 00:09:57,120
and capable

226
00:09:57,600 --> 00:09:59,030
to bring her back?

227
00:10:02,150 --> 00:10:02,990
Where's Chubby?

228
00:11:14,120 --> 00:11:16,240
Chubby! Chubby!

229
00:11:17,550 --> 00:11:18,630
What are you doing?

230
00:11:54,720 --> 00:11:56,150
Chubby, run!

231
00:11:56,390 --> 00:11:58,270
Run, Chubby!

232
00:11:59,320 --> 00:12:00,870
Run!

233
00:12:08,750 --> 00:12:09,590
Go!

234
00:12:13,740 --> 00:12:17,340
(Xiangmu, Princess Xian'an)

235
00:12:33,630 --> 00:12:34,600
- Lu.
- Sit.

236
00:12:35,720 --> 00:12:36,560
Sit here.

237
00:12:37,510 --> 00:12:38,480
I was scared.

238
00:12:39,030 --> 00:12:41,440
Oh, my. That was close.

239
00:12:42,390 --> 00:12:43,240
Lu,

240
00:12:43,270 --> 00:12:44,870
why were you lying still just now?

241
00:12:46,080 --> 00:12:48,080
I haven't enjoyed enough of my life,

242
00:12:48,200 --> 00:12:49,670
and you almost got me killed.

243
00:12:50,150 --> 00:12:51,790
My legs were weak.

244
00:12:52,630 --> 00:12:53,490
Chubby,

245
00:12:53,510 --> 00:12:55,360
luckily, you pulled me.

246
00:12:55,550 --> 00:12:57,240
You saved my life.

247
00:12:57,510 --> 00:12:59,030
Next life, I'll be a girl

248
00:12:59,030 --> 00:13:00,120
and marry you.

249
00:13:00,910 --> 00:13:02,080
Stop being gross.

250
00:13:02,320 --> 00:13:03,270
Just stay put.

251
00:13:05,080 --> 00:13:06,550
What exactly is that?

252
00:13:06,840 --> 00:13:07,720
A spider?

253
00:13:07,960 --> 00:13:08,800
A Ghost-Face Spider.

254
00:13:08,960 --> 00:13:09,840
What?

255
00:13:09,840 --> 00:13:11,740
A spider with a human-face pattern
on its body.

256
00:13:13,120 --> 00:13:14,240
It's huge.

257
00:13:14,240 --> 00:13:15,630
How did it grow so big?

258
00:13:15,630 --> 00:13:16,899
It was born in the Tang dynasty.

259
00:13:16,910 --> 00:13:17,910
Not surprising.

260
00:13:18,390 --> 00:13:19,630
The Tang dynasty...

261
00:13:19,960 --> 00:13:22,750
Still alive now?

262
00:13:24,200 --> 00:13:25,080
Where's Bai Lingling?

263
00:13:30,600 --> 00:13:31,440
Sorry.

264
00:14:01,960 --> 00:14:02,840
That girl...

265
00:14:03,510 --> 00:14:04,550
Chubby, Chubby!

266
00:14:04,670 --> 00:14:05,870
Chen Youxi, I'll go too.

267
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:07,120
You stay and take care of Lu.

268
00:14:09,870 --> 00:14:10,750
Be careful.

269
00:14:14,840 --> 00:14:16,630
Those two are too daring.

270
00:14:17,550 --> 00:14:20,720
Risking their lives for a girl.

271
00:14:21,070 --> 00:14:21,960
Ms. He,

272
00:14:21,960 --> 00:14:23,440
you should have stopped them.

273
00:14:23,440 --> 00:14:24,910
Don't you have better things to do?

274
00:14:30,280 --> 00:14:31,120
Well, Ms. He.

275
00:14:31,120 --> 00:14:32,200
I didn't mean that.

276
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:34,510
Youxi is a good comrade.

277
00:14:34,720 --> 00:14:36,320
But Li Ke is no good.

278
00:14:36,960 --> 00:14:38,269
You can tell by that girl's eyes

279
00:14:38,280 --> 00:14:39,870
that she's trouble.

280
00:14:40,080 --> 00:14:42,440
Introduce a good girl to Li Ke,

281
00:14:42,440 --> 00:14:43,870
so he doesn't pick badly.

282
00:14:50,510 --> 00:14:51,350
She got hurt.

283
00:15:03,360 --> 00:15:05,320
You're too disobedient,

284
00:15:05,496 --> 00:15:06,670
leaving the team on your own.

285
00:15:06,670 --> 00:15:07,996
Do you know how dangerous that is?

286
00:15:08,390 --> 00:15:09,230
Sit here.

287
00:15:09,630 --> 00:15:10,480
Does it hurt?

288
00:15:12,150 --> 00:15:13,080
What happened?

289
00:15:13,080 --> 00:15:14,030
Shutong, check her.

290
00:15:17,840 --> 00:15:18,840
Leave us alone.

291
00:15:30,000 --> 00:15:31,000
This jerk.

292
00:15:31,320 --> 00:15:32,600
My little cannon

293
00:15:32,870 --> 00:15:34,120
didn't kill it.

294
00:15:37,080 --> 00:15:38,910
I noticed this giant spider

295
00:15:39,200 --> 00:15:40,200
only walks

296
00:15:40,440 --> 00:15:43,030
to that stone tablet

297
00:15:43,360 --> 00:15:44,240
and then retreats.

298
00:15:45,750 --> 00:15:47,240
It seems true.

299
00:16:08,320 --> 00:16:11,030
You must hate it that I'm not hurt.

300
00:16:14,000 --> 00:16:15,960
I don't care about that.

301
00:16:16,270 --> 00:16:17,240
But let me tell you:

302
00:16:17,440 --> 00:16:19,240
If you act alone again,

303
00:16:20,030 --> 00:16:21,510
